Completion of this class will give the student a certificate of completion  necessary when applying for a concealed carry permit. New shooters are welcome to attend but are encouraged to seek live fire training and/or practice with an instructor or with experienced shooters.   You must be 21 years of age. No Ammunition in class.

NRA Basic Pistol Shooting Course $150.00
 Teaches the basic knowledge, skills, and attitude for owning and operating a pistol safely.
 This course includes classroom and range time learning to shoot revolvers and semi-automatic pistols. Students learn NRA’s rules for safe gun handling; pistol parts and operation; ammunition; shooting fundamentals; range rules; shooting from the bench rest position, and two handed standing positions; cleaning the pistol; and continued opportunities for skill development. Students will receive the NRA Guide to the Basics of Pistol Shooting handbook, NRA Gun Safety Rules brochure, Winchester/NRA Marksmanship Qualification booklet, take a Basics of Pistol Shooting Student Examination, and course completion certificate. The live fire potion of this course you will be shooting .22 caliber handgun in order to practice and learn basic marksmanship skills and qualifications. You are welcome to bring your own handgun and ammunition.
